OL,3,CCriminal justice delays 'worse than
OL,4,CI've ever known them to be', CPS head
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FHe went on to condemn delays faced by
OL,8,Fvictims, who are facing waits of
OL,9,Fbetween two and five years to see a
OL,10,Fcase go to trial, with some court
OL,11,Flistings now running into 2027.
OL,13,FMr Parkinson said it could take
OL,14,Froughly 700 days on average - almost
OL,15,Ftwo years - from the point of an
OL,16,Fallegation being reported to police
OL,17,Ffor rape victims to see their case
OL,18,Fconcluded.
